uk.ac.ebi.pridemod.model

Class Specificity

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pridemod.model.Specificity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable

    public class Specificity
extends Object
implements Comparable
    Specificity is a class that contains the information of the aminoacid specificity for modifications and also specified the position of this amino acids (N-term, C-Term) or Anywhere. The class contains inside a two classes to define the position and the amino acid specificity.
